cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with natural language generation and comprehension for objects in images, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of a comprehension module to guide the generation of referring expressions suggests a focus on natural language processing, which is why cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The use of image data and the need to identify objects in images suggests a focus on computer vision, which is why cs.CV is also likely. The use of models and training signals suggests a focus on artificial intelligence, which is why cs.AI is also likely. The use of benchmarks and evaluation criteria suggests a focus on machine learning, which is why cs.LG is also likely. Finally, the use of a generate-and-rerank pipeline suggests a focus on information retrieval, which is why cs.IR is also likely.
